window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The Montgomery Ink series from <i>NYT</i> Best-selling Author Carrie Ann Ryan continues with the brother who keeps his silence and the one woman he shouldn't want. </b></p> <p><b>Everly Law</b> married the love of her life, and on the eve of giving birth to their twins, lost him in a tragic accident. Now she's a single mother working overtime at her bookstore trying to give her boys the life they deserve. Her life is demanding enough without her adding a Montgomery to the mix. But as past secrets come to light, she'll need Storm more than ever - even if she doesn't want to admit it. </p> <p><b>Storm Montgomery</b> has spent his life atoning for sins that few know he committed. When he lost his best friend, he promised Jackson's widow he would always be there for her - even when she seemingly wanted nothing to do with him. But when a single touch ignites passions they've both kept buried deep inside, he'll have to remember exactly who is in his arms, and that taking chances might be far more dangerous than either of them bargained for. </p>"; 
